WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.936 align:middle line:90%


00:00:07.936 --> 00:00:11.904 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:11.904 --> 00:00:32.280 align:middle line:90%


00:00:32.280 --> 00:00:35.220 align:middle line:90%
>> My name is Craig Anderson.

00:00:35.220 --> 00:00:37.890 align:middle line:84%
I'm a 38-year-old
actor and filmmaker,

00:00:37.890 --> 00:00:41.713 align:middle line:90%
and I live in Sydney, Australia.

00:00:41.713 --> 00:00:43.880 align:middle line:84%
And though you probably
can't tell by looking at me,

00:00:43.880 --> 00:00:48.270 align:middle line:90%
I'm a little bit overweight.

00:00:48.270 --> 00:00:52.170 align:middle line:84%
This is my castle, my
fortress of solitude.

00:00:52.170 --> 00:00:55.060 align:middle line:84%
It's a combination of creative
arts studio and open plan

00:00:55.060 --> 00:01:00.600 align:middle line:84%
living space, better
known as a warehouse.

00:01:00.600 --> 00:01:03.850 align:middle line:84%
It's here that I pursue my
dream of being a filmmaker.

00:01:03.850 --> 00:01:06.760 align:middle line:84%
I write, act in, and edit
a lot of my own material,

00:01:06.760 --> 00:01:10.540 align:middle line:84%
and this is where
the magic happens.

00:01:10.540 --> 00:01:12.710 align:middle line:90%
But being creative isn't easy.

00:01:12.710 --> 00:01:15.948 align:middle line:84%
It requires stimulation of
both the mind and the body.

00:01:15.948 --> 00:01:17.740 align:middle line:84%
And that's why I start
each day with a trip

00:01:17.740 --> 00:01:18.880 align:middle line:90%
to the local swimming pool.

00:01:18.880 --> 00:01:28.380 align:middle line:90%


00:01:28.380 --> 00:01:29.180 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:01:29.180 --> 00:01:32.780 align:middle line:84%
So this is the
warehouse where I live.

00:01:32.780 --> 00:01:38.345 align:middle line:84%
And I'm now driving
to the local pool/gym.

00:01:38.345 --> 00:01:41.180 align:middle line:90%


00:01:41.180 --> 00:01:42.230 align:middle line:90%
It's got everything.

00:01:42.230 --> 00:01:44.600 align:middle line:84%
But most importantly
it has a shower.

00:01:44.600 --> 00:01:50.030 align:middle line:84%
And my warehouse only
has cold water shower so.

00:01:50.030 --> 00:01:53.420 align:middle line:84%
Every few days my daily
routine is to drive to the pool

00:01:53.420 --> 00:01:57.680 align:middle line:90%
and have a shower there.

00:01:57.680 --> 00:02:00.920 align:middle line:84%
This might seem inconvenient,
but it beats a cold shower.

00:02:00.920 --> 00:02:03.950 align:middle line:84%
Plus, it gets me out of the
house, which, let's face it,

00:02:03.950 --> 00:02:07.887 align:middle line:84%
is pretty much my only
exercise for the day.

00:02:07.887 --> 00:02:10.220 align:middle line:84%
After avoiding weird glances
from people who've actually

00:02:10.220 --> 00:02:12.260 align:middle line:90%
been in the pool, I head home.

00:02:12.260 --> 00:02:16.100 align:middle line:90%
Time for breakfast.

00:02:16.100 --> 00:02:19.000 align:middle line:84%
Working long hours takes
energy, and creative work

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:20.250 align:middle line:90%
is no different.

00:02:20.250 --> 00:02:23.540 align:middle line:84%
So I like to start the day
with a big, hearty breakfast.

00:02:23.540 --> 00:02:25.460 align:middle line:84%
A well-rounded
diet is important,

00:02:25.460 --> 00:02:28.460 align:middle line:84%
so I try to include all
the important food groups--

00:02:28.460 --> 00:02:31.880 align:middle line:84%
bacon, eggs,
sausages, hash browns,

00:02:31.880 --> 00:02:33.540 align:middle line:90%
and a serving of Froot--

00:02:33.540 --> 00:02:34.340 align:middle line:90%
Loops.

00:02:34.340 --> 00:02:37.570 align:middle line:90%


00:02:37.570 --> 00:02:41.430 align:middle line:84%
I'm clean, I'm fed, and
it's time to get to work.

00:02:41.430 --> 00:02:42.230 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:02:42.230 --> 00:02:44.750 align:middle line:90%
Well, this is my room.

00:02:44.750 --> 00:02:47.240 align:middle line:84%
When I finish at the
pool, I come back here

00:02:47.240 --> 00:02:52.730 align:middle line:84%
and that's my bed, which
I haven't put away.

00:02:52.730 --> 00:02:55.340 align:middle line:84%
I sleep on the floor
on this mattress,

00:02:55.340 --> 00:02:58.040 align:middle line:84%
but I put it in the
corner during the day

00:02:58.040 --> 00:03:01.130 align:middle line:84%
so that potential
clients who come in

00:03:01.130 --> 00:03:03.380 align:middle line:84%
to check out the edits
that I've been doing

00:03:03.380 --> 00:03:05.930 align:middle line:90%
don't think that I'm a hobo.

00:03:05.930 --> 00:03:08.840 align:middle line:84%
That being said, I do have a
clothes rack in the corner.

00:03:08.840 --> 00:03:09.950 align:middle line:90%
No one ever says anything.

00:03:09.950 --> 00:03:11.210 align:middle line:90%
I don't know why.

00:03:11.210 --> 00:03:14.155 align:middle line:90%
I keep my clothes.

00:03:14.155 --> 00:03:18.130 align:middle line:84%
This is where the fresh clothes
go and the used clothes.

00:03:18.130 --> 00:03:18.930 align:middle line:90%
I won't open that.

00:03:18.930 --> 00:03:20.900 align:middle line:90%
That's in there.

00:03:20.900 --> 00:03:26.395 align:middle line:84%
And this is my edit suite, where
I sit pretty much all the time.

00:03:26.395 --> 00:03:27.770 align:middle line:84%
Maybe once a week
I get to go out

00:03:27.770 --> 00:03:29.990 align:middle line:84%
and actually shoot
something, which is fun.

00:03:29.990 --> 00:03:33.110 align:middle line:84%
But most of the time I
sit here at the control

00:03:33.110 --> 00:03:37.655 align:middle line:84%
tower and edit exciting
film and TV projects.

00:03:37.655 --> 00:03:41.850 align:middle line:90%


00:03:41.850 --> 00:03:44.550 align:middle line:84%
Video editing is a
time intensive job.

00:03:44.550 --> 00:03:47.550 align:middle line:84%
And it's normal for me to sit in
my edit suite for hours on end,

00:03:47.550 --> 00:03:51.228 align:middle line:84%
getting up to only go to
the bathroom or to eat.

00:03:51.228 --> 00:03:52.770 align:middle line:84%
And I often work
late into the night,

00:03:52.770 --> 00:03:55.360 align:middle line:84%
which means my dinner
options can be very limited.

00:03:55.360 --> 00:03:59.790 align:middle line:90%


00:03:59.790 --> 00:04:00.590 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:04:00.590 --> 00:04:02.330 align:middle line:90%
Well, it's 11:30 at night.

00:04:02.330 --> 00:04:04.880 align:middle line:84%
And I finished
some editing, which

00:04:04.880 --> 00:04:06.540 align:middle line:90%
is great, because I nailed it.

00:04:06.540 --> 00:04:09.590 align:middle line:90%
But it's 11:30 at night.

00:04:09.590 --> 00:04:11.480 align:middle line:84%
And obviously, all
the places that

00:04:11.480 --> 00:04:14.000 align:middle line:84%
should be open where
you can buy food

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:18.399 align:middle line:84%
are now closed, which means
I don't have many options.

00:04:18.399 --> 00:04:19.970 align:middle line:84%
There's convenience
stores, where

00:04:19.970 --> 00:04:24.450 align:middle line:84%
I could get a sausage
roll and a flavored milk.

00:04:24.450 --> 00:04:27.770 align:middle line:90%
Or there's McDonald's.

00:04:27.770 --> 00:04:29.932 align:middle line:90%
So I'm going to McDonald's.

00:04:29.932 --> 00:04:35.350 align:middle line:90%


00:04:35.350 --> 00:04:37.090 align:middle line:90%
Back from McDonald's.

00:04:37.090 --> 00:04:44.080 align:middle line:84%
And I got the beef value
meal, because value.

00:04:44.080 --> 00:04:46.660 align:middle line:84%
You get a whole
bunch of burgers.

00:04:46.660 --> 00:04:49.570 align:middle line:84%
Which is good, because
I'll eat a few of them now.

00:04:49.570 --> 00:04:53.320 align:middle line:84%
And then the ones that don't get
through I can put in the fridge

00:04:53.320 --> 00:04:57.760 align:middle line:84%
and I have for lunch or
for breakfast tomorrow.

00:04:57.760 --> 00:05:00.580 align:middle line:90%
So yeah.

00:05:00.580 --> 00:05:02.050 align:middle line:90%
It's economic sense.

00:05:02.050 --> 00:05:05.450 align:middle line:90%


00:05:05.450 --> 00:05:06.940 align:middle line:90%
So there you have it--

00:05:06.940 --> 00:05:08.920 align:middle line:90%
a snapshot of my life.

00:05:08.920 --> 00:05:12.050 align:middle line:84%
You might find it strange,
but I'm doing what I love.

00:05:12.050 --> 00:05:13.060 align:middle line:90%
I'm chasing my dreams.

00:05:13.060 --> 00:05:16.390 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of the day, I
wouldn't trade it for anything.

00:05:16.390 --> 00:05:19.186 align:middle line:84%
The only problem
is, it's killing me.

00:05:19.186 --> 00:05:31.340 align:middle line:90%


00:05:31.340 --> 00:05:33.380 align:middle line:90%
Another day, another burger.

00:05:33.380 --> 00:05:36.952 align:middle line:84%
In a typical week I'll eat at
least four fast food meals.

00:05:36.952 --> 00:05:38.660 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how much
of it's convenience

00:05:38.660 --> 00:05:40.730 align:middle line:90%
and how much is addiction.

00:05:40.730 --> 00:05:42.220 align:middle line:90%
I'm not sure I want to know.

00:05:42.220 --> 00:05:46.070 align:middle line:84%
And when I do cook for myself,
it's usually just as bad.

00:05:46.070 --> 00:05:49.170 align:middle line:84%
I decided to keep a record
of my eating habits.

00:05:49.170 --> 00:05:50.690 align:middle line:90%
It's not pretty.

00:05:50.690 --> 00:05:55.550 align:middle line:84%
Pizza, burgers, fries, all kinds
of sweets, and gallons of soda.

00:05:55.550 --> 00:05:57.110 align:middle line:90%
And that's just in one week.

00:05:57.110 --> 00:06:01.660 align:middle line:90%


00:06:01.660 --> 00:06:04.750 align:middle line:84%
I know how bad this is for
me, but I can't seem to stop.

00:06:04.750 --> 00:06:06.790 align:middle line:84%
I've tried every
died under the sun.

00:06:06.790 --> 00:06:09.200 align:middle line:84%
But in the end the results
are always the same.

00:06:09.200 --> 00:06:11.500 align:middle line:84%
The diet becomes
impractical to maintain,

00:06:11.500 --> 00:06:14.860 align:middle line:90%
and I fall off the wagon.

00:06:14.860 --> 00:06:18.490 align:middle line:84%
I know I need to change,
but I really don't know how.

00:06:18.490 --> 00:06:21.980 align:middle line:84%
Fortunately, the change
I needed found me.

00:06:21.980 --> 00:06:22.780 align:middle line:90%
Hang on.

00:06:22.780 --> 00:06:24.190 align:middle line:90%
Like the country?

00:06:24.190 --> 00:06:25.000 align:middle line:90%
Japan the country?

00:06:25.000 --> 00:06:26.080 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:06:26.080 --> 00:06:29.490 align:middle line:90%
No, I've never been before.

00:06:29.490 --> 00:06:31.860 align:middle line:84%
A few weeks ago I was
contacted by my friend

00:06:31.860 --> 00:06:33.900 align:middle line:90%
Tim, a fellow filmmaker.

00:06:33.900 --> 00:06:36.360 align:middle line:84%
He told me he wanted to make
a documentary about the health

00:06:36.360 --> 00:06:39.720 align:middle line:84%
benefits of the
Japanese lifestyle.

00:06:39.720 --> 00:06:41.220 align:middle line:84%
As someone who grew
up in Japan, he

00:06:41.220 --> 00:06:43.410 align:middle line:84%
knows how different their
food culture is compared

00:06:43.410 --> 00:06:45.720 align:middle line:90%
to the typical Western diet.

00:06:45.720 --> 00:06:47.310 align:middle line:90%
His idea was this--

00:06:47.310 --> 00:06:49.200 align:middle line:84%
send someone to
Japan for two weeks

00:06:49.200 --> 00:06:51.900 align:middle line:84%
to learn how the
Japanese live and eat.

00:06:51.900 --> 00:06:55.050 align:middle line:84%
Then have them return home
and recreate that lifestyle

00:06:55.050 --> 00:06:57.660 align:middle line:84%
for a further 10 weeks
and see what effect

00:06:57.660 --> 00:07:01.850 align:middle line:84%
this three-month Japanese
diet has on their health.

00:07:01.850 --> 00:07:04.340 align:middle line:84%
For some reason
he thought of me.

00:07:04.340 --> 00:07:07.990 align:middle line:84%
Probably because
of my good looks.

00:07:07.990 --> 00:07:10.510 align:middle line:84%
After talking to Tim,
I did a little research

00:07:10.510 --> 00:07:13.937 align:middle line:90%
on Japanese health.

00:07:13.937 --> 00:07:15.770 align:middle line:84%
I found out that they
had some of the lowest

00:07:15.770 --> 00:07:20.900 align:middle line:84%
rates of obesity and heart
disease in the developed world.

00:07:20.900 --> 00:07:22.910 align:middle line:84%
They also have a
very low cancer rate.

00:07:22.910 --> 00:07:25.390 align:middle line:90%


00:07:25.390 --> 00:07:27.890 align:middle line:84%
The weird thing is, they don't
seem to skimp on their meals.

00:07:27.890 --> 00:07:29.780 align:middle line:84%
They are eating all
the time, and it's

00:07:29.780 --> 00:07:31.770 align:middle line:90%
a part of their culture.

00:07:31.770 --> 00:07:34.250 align:middle line:84%
So how is it a nation that
is so devoted to stuffing

00:07:34.250 --> 00:07:36.740 align:middle line:84%
their faces is amongst
the healthiest?

00:07:36.740 --> 00:07:38.480 align:middle line:84%
What is it about their
diet and lifestyle

00:07:38.480 --> 00:07:41.570 align:middle line:84%
that lets them live such
long and healthy lives?

00:07:41.570 --> 00:07:42.920 align:middle line:90%
I was intrigued.

00:07:42.920 --> 00:07:45.800 align:middle line:90%
So I told Tim I was in.

00:07:45.800 --> 00:07:47.390 align:middle line:84%
But before the fun
could start, there

00:07:47.390 --> 00:07:51.710 align:middle line:84%
were a few things I
had to take care of.

00:07:51.710 --> 00:07:52.510 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:07:52.510 --> 00:07:53.080 align:middle line:90%
Are we ready?

00:07:53.080 --> 00:07:53.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, yeah.

00:07:53.610 --> 00:07:54.460 align:middle line:90%
I love blood tests.

00:07:54.460 --> 00:07:55.100 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:07:55.100 --> 00:07:55.630 align:middle line:90%
>> All right.

00:07:55.630 --> 00:07:55.970 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:07:55.970 --> 00:07:56.770 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:07:56.770 --> 00:07:57.800 align:middle line:90%
>> Just very still.

00:07:57.800 --> 00:07:57.910 align:middle line:90%
>> All right.

00:07:57.910 --> 00:07:58.720 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:07:58.720 --> 00:08:01.222 align:middle line:90%
Great.

00:08:01.222 --> 00:08:03.430 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm doing some medical
tests before I leave to get

00:08:03.430 --> 00:08:05.740 align:middle line:90%
a snapshot of my overall health.

00:08:05.740 --> 00:08:08.710 align:middle line:84%
Once the diet is over I'll
come back and do the same tests

00:08:08.710 --> 00:08:10.360 align:middle line:90%
and compare the results.

00:08:10.360 --> 00:08:13.180 align:middle line:84%
This should provide a very
clear picture of what effect

00:08:13.180 --> 00:08:16.330 align:middle line:90%
that diet has had on my body.

00:08:16.330 --> 00:08:17.950 align:middle line:90%
How is my health in general?

00:08:17.950 --> 00:08:19.870 align:middle line:90%
Obviously it's not the best.

00:08:19.870 --> 00:08:21.520 align:middle line:90%
>> We've got your baseline here.

00:08:21.520 --> 00:08:24.320 align:middle line:84%
And there are some
areas of concern.

00:08:24.320 --> 00:08:29.080 align:middle line:84%
The most obvious one is
this red number here 4GGT.

00:08:29.080 --> 00:08:31.390 align:middle line:90%
And that is a liver enzyme.

00:08:31.390 --> 00:08:36.070 align:middle line:84%
This particular enzyme lives
inside a healthy liver cell

00:08:36.070 --> 00:08:39.190 align:middle line:84%
and does its toxic
waste recycling job.

00:08:39.190 --> 00:08:41.169 align:middle line:84%
When that liver
cell is damaged, it

00:08:41.169 --> 00:08:43.330 align:middle line:84%
releases this into
the bloodstream,

00:08:43.330 --> 00:08:44.650 align:middle line:90%
and then we measure it.

00:08:44.650 --> 00:08:48.230 align:middle line:84%
And yours has come back out
of reference range for that.

00:08:48.230 --> 00:08:49.120 align:middle line:90%
>> Out of reference?

00:08:49.120 --> 00:08:50.230 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:08:50.230 --> 00:08:52.780 align:middle line:84%
Yours is high out
of range, and that

00:08:52.780 --> 00:08:56.530 align:middle line:84%
would indicate an excessive
inflammation of your liver.

00:08:56.530 --> 00:08:58.750 align:middle line:84%
That can be due to
a lot of reasons.

00:08:58.750 --> 00:09:01.990 align:middle line:84%
But sometimes just
carrying extra weight

00:09:01.990 --> 00:09:05.410 align:middle line:84%
and perhaps having a very
high refined sugar diet

00:09:05.410 --> 00:09:08.770 align:middle line:84%
will actually promote that
extra demand on the liver,

00:09:08.770 --> 00:09:11.170 align:middle line:84%
damage those liver cells,
and then show this sort

00:09:11.170 --> 00:09:12.350 align:middle line:90%
of result on the blood test.

00:09:12.350 --> 00:09:22.200 align:middle line:90%


00:09:22.200 --> 00:09:24.330 align:middle line:84%
>> This diet is about
more than just weight.

00:09:24.330 --> 00:09:26.880 align:middle line:90%
It's about improving my health.

00:09:26.880 --> 00:09:29.820 align:middle line:84%
That's why I'm doing
this bio-impedance test.

00:09:29.820 --> 00:09:33.210 align:middle line:84%
Developed by NASA, the test
measures the biological age

00:09:33.210 --> 00:09:34.380 align:middle line:90%
of the patient.

00:09:34.380 --> 00:09:38.520 align:middle line:84%
And I think I'll be pleasantly
surprised with the results.

00:09:38.520 --> 00:09:42.130 align:middle line:84%
>> The healthy body weight for
you should sit between that red

00:09:42.130 --> 00:09:45.640 align:middle line:90%
line there, around 72 up to 75.

00:09:45.640 --> 00:09:48.010 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately,
this is you here.

00:09:48.010 --> 00:09:49.390 align:middle line:90%
>> I look like the timeline.

00:09:49.390 --> 00:09:51.340 align:middle line:90%
>> Just a little bit overweight.

00:09:51.340 --> 00:09:54.460 align:middle line:84%
So that's something that
needs to be looked at.

00:09:54.460 --> 00:09:59.020 align:middle line:84%
The bad news is when we
look at your biological age,

00:09:59.020 --> 00:10:02.140 align:middle line:84%
you've ticked in
at 64 years of age.

00:10:02.140 --> 00:10:06.383 align:middle line:84%
The good news is that all
of this is reversible.

00:10:06.383 --> 00:10:07.300 align:middle line:90%
>> I get to keep this?

00:10:07.300 --> 00:10:08.200 align:middle line:90%
>> You get to keep that.

00:10:08.200 --> 00:10:08.920 align:middle line:90%
>> I get to keep that.

00:10:08.920 --> 00:10:09.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:10:09.850 --> 00:10:14.830 align:middle line:84%
>> How very exciting for
me to have this document.

00:10:14.830 --> 00:10:17.860 align:middle line:84%
My exam results weren't
as pretty as this footage.

00:10:17.860 --> 00:10:19.960 align:middle line:90%
Here's how I shape up.

00:10:19.960 --> 00:10:23.410 align:middle line:90%
I weigh a whopping 138 kilos.

00:10:23.410 --> 00:10:25.400 align:middle line:84%
And although I'm
only 38 years old,

00:10:25.400 --> 00:10:29.290 align:middle line:84%
I have the liver of a
64-year-old heavy drinker.

00:10:29.290 --> 00:10:32.080 align:middle line:84%
My high processed sugar
diet has caused my liver

00:10:32.080 --> 00:10:34.120 align:middle line:90%
to have serious inflammation.

00:10:34.120 --> 00:10:35.590 align:middle line:84%
And the enzyme
levels on the liver

00:10:35.590 --> 00:10:39.820 align:middle line:84%
function tests were completely
out of reference range.

00:10:39.820 --> 00:10:43.400 align:middle line:84%
I'm also at risk of future
cardiovascular disease,

00:10:43.400 --> 00:10:46.190 align:middle line:84%
particularly heart
attacks and strokes.

00:10:46.190 --> 00:10:48.460 align:middle line:84%
There's a thing called
a C-reactive protein

00:10:48.460 --> 00:10:52.150 align:middle line:84%
level, which is a good indicator
of cardiovascular risk.

00:10:52.150 --> 00:10:54.820 align:middle line:84%
Ideally you want
to score below 1.

