OK.

00:50:26.870 --> 00:50:29.420 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, but that's
what I'm eating.

00:50:29.420 --> 00:50:31.240 align:middle line:84%
And I've got some
green tea here as well.

00:50:31.240 --> 00:50:36.070 align:middle line:90%


00:50:36.070 --> 00:50:38.620 align:middle line:84%
I've gotten into the habit
of shopping for groceries

00:50:38.620 --> 00:50:41.230 align:middle line:84%
instead of relying
on premade meals.

00:50:41.230 --> 00:50:43.510 align:middle line:84%
This will be invaluable
when I have to keep

00:50:43.510 --> 00:50:46.500 align:middle line:90%
the diet going back home.

00:50:46.500 --> 00:50:47.920 align:middle line:90%
Hey.

00:50:47.920 --> 00:50:50.980 align:middle line:84%
I just went to get some
water and some natto

00:50:50.980 --> 00:50:53.980 align:middle line:90%
at the convenience store.

00:50:53.980 --> 00:50:56.813 align:middle line:84%
I've put my jeans on
today, which is exciting.

00:50:56.813 --> 00:50:59.230 align:middle line:84%
Not because they're jeans, but
because I haven't worn them

00:50:59.230 --> 00:51:01.823 align:middle line:84%
for a while, and they
are feeling loose.

00:51:01.823 --> 00:51:04.240 align:middle line:84%
Which is good, because when I
wore them a couple of months

00:51:04.240 --> 00:51:08.440 align:middle line:84%
ago before I started this whole
process, they were very tight.

00:51:08.440 --> 00:51:10.840 align:middle line:84%
So I think I've lost some
weight around the waist, which

00:51:10.840 --> 00:51:11.640 align:middle line:90%
is good.

00:51:11.640 --> 00:51:19.030 align:middle line:90%


00:51:19.030 --> 00:51:20.890 align:middle line:84%
The whole time I've
been here, I haven't

00:51:20.890 --> 00:51:22.810 align:middle line:90%
seen any overweight people--

00:51:22.810 --> 00:51:25.285 align:middle line:90%
certainly no one as big as me.

00:51:25.285 --> 00:51:27.160 align:middle line:84%
I was wondering, what
are the locals thinking

00:51:27.160 --> 00:51:31.780 align:middle line:84%
when they see someone my size,
when all of a sudden it hit me.

00:51:31.780 --> 00:51:34.520 align:middle line:84%
There are people
this size in Japan.

00:51:34.520 --> 00:51:39.280 align:middle line:84%
In fact, they're much bigger
in every possible way.

00:51:39.280 --> 00:51:42.220 align:middle line:84%
Sumo wrestlers are
cultural icons.

00:51:42.220 --> 00:51:46.130 align:middle line:84%
And the majority of them are
still born and raised in Japan.

00:51:46.130 --> 00:51:50.350 align:middle line:84%
So what are they eating in order
to reach their massive size?

00:51:50.350 --> 00:51:53.770 align:middle line:84%
I asked the crew to arrange a
meeting with a sumo wrestler.

00:51:53.770 --> 00:51:57.490 align:middle line:84%
And as it turns out, they got
the biggest one of all time.

00:51:57.490 --> 00:52:01.361 align:middle line:90%


00:52:01.361 --> 00:52:04.240 align:middle line:90%
Konishiki is a sumo legend.

00:52:04.240 --> 00:52:07.240 align:middle line:84%
Born in Hawaii, he's
a three-time champion

00:52:07.240 --> 00:52:10.810 align:middle line:84%
and holds the record for the
heaviest sumo wrestler ever.

00:52:10.810 --> 00:52:15.190 align:middle line:84%
If anyone could tell me what
to avoid in my diet, it's him.

00:52:15.190 --> 00:52:16.990 align:middle line:84%
I'm just hoping
he won't be angry

00:52:16.990 --> 00:52:22.680 align:middle line:84%
when I ask him what I should be
doing to not end up like him.

00:52:22.680 --> 00:52:24.290 align:middle line:84%
Did you notice a
difference in food

00:52:24.290 --> 00:52:26.810 align:middle line:90%
between here and Samoa, Hawaii?

00:52:26.810 --> 00:52:29.278 align:middle line:84%
>> Well the food here
is great, you know,

00:52:29.278 --> 00:52:31.820 align:middle line:84%
even though at the beginning my
career there were some things

00:52:31.820 --> 00:52:33.470 align:middle line:90%
that I couldn't eat, like natto.

00:52:33.470 --> 00:52:34.520 align:middle line:90%
Natto is that--

00:52:34.520 --> 00:52:35.480 align:middle line:90%
>> I know natto.

00:52:35.480 --> 00:52:36.800 align:middle line:90%
I eat it every morning now.

00:52:36.800 --> 00:52:38.190 align:middle line:90%
>> I love it.

00:52:38.190 --> 00:52:40.460 align:middle line:84%
I love it now, but I couldn't
eat it before, natto.

00:52:40.460 --> 00:52:44.270 align:middle line:84%
The tofu wasn't
something I ate before.

00:52:44.270 --> 00:52:48.290 align:middle line:84%
But, you know, I think Japan has
a very healthy diet naturally.

00:52:48.290 --> 00:52:49.400 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, I've noticed.

00:52:49.400 --> 00:52:51.390 align:middle line:84%
It's much easier for
me to eat healthy here.

00:52:51.390 --> 00:52:52.190 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:52:52.190 --> 00:52:53.055 align:middle line:90%
>> A lot easier.

00:52:53.055 --> 00:52:55.430 align:middle line:84%
>> And you notice, everything
that comes with Japan food,

00:52:55.430 --> 00:52:56.570 align:middle line:90%
there's always vegetables.

00:52:56.570 --> 00:52:57.370 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:52:57.370 --> 00:52:58.880 align:middle line:90%
>> Always vegetables.

00:52:58.880 --> 00:53:01.220 align:middle line:84%
