00:53:11.180 --> 00:53:13.280 align:middle line:90%
It can be like kimchi.

00:53:13.280 --> 00:53:16.970 align:middle line:84%
And then you add meat to
it, maybe pork, or beef,

00:53:16.970 --> 00:53:18.310 align:middle line:90%
or seafood.

00:53:18.310 --> 00:53:19.110 align:middle line:90%
It don't matter.

00:53:19.110 --> 00:53:19.790 align:middle line:90%
Chicken.

00:53:19.790 --> 00:53:20.590 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:53:20.590 --> 00:53:22.250 align:middle line:90%
>> So it's like a stew.

00:53:22.250 --> 00:53:23.280 align:middle line:90%
>> It sounds--

00:53:23.280 --> 00:53:24.080 align:middle line:90%
>> It's healthy.

00:53:24.080 --> 00:53:25.247 align:middle line:90%
>> It sounds healthy, right?

00:53:25.247 --> 00:53:28.040 align:middle line:84%
>> It's not the food
that really gets us big.

00:53:28.040 --> 00:53:31.760 align:middle line:84%
>> It turns out sumo wrestlers
eat similar types of food

00:53:31.760 --> 00:53:33.860 align:middle line:90%
