>> I don't think so.

00:58:10.000 --> 00:58:10.800 align:middle line:90%
>> OK.

00:58:10.800 --> 00:58:11.410 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:58:11.410 --> 00:58:12.452 align:middle line:90%
It was probably too much.

00:58:12.452 --> 00:58:20.222 align:middle line:90%


00:58:20.222 --> 00:58:21.180 align:middle line:90%
>> To drop on the rice.

00:58:21.180 --> 00:58:25.110 align:middle line:84%
So it's like using,
instead of a hand--

00:58:25.110 --> 00:58:27.790 align:middle line:90%
>> So I can do this.

00:58:27.790 --> 00:58:28.590 align:middle line:90%
And I look good?

00:58:28.590 --> 00:58:28.940 align:middle line:90%
>> Mm-hmm.

00:58:28.940 --> 00:58:29.670 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:58:29.670 --> 00:58:30.628 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, and you drop it.

00:58:30.628 --> 00:58:37.690 align:middle line:90%


00:58:37.690 --> 00:58:40.810 align:middle line:84%
>> My meeting with Mr. Otaka has
shown me that cheap, healthy,

00:58:40.810 --> 00:58:43.980 align:middle line:84%
nutritious food choices
are abundant everywhere,

00:58:43.980 --> 00:58:46.680 align:middle line:84%
even in places you
would never expect.

00:58:46.680 --> 00:58:50.100 align:middle line:84%
The Japanese culture seems to
promote a healthy lifestyle,

00:58:50.100 --> 00:58:53.850 align:middle line:84%
even in locations where greasy,
fried foods would be so much

00:58:53.850 --> 00:58:55.860 align:middle line:90%
easier to serve.

00:58:55.860 --> 00:58:58.380 align:middle line:84%
I don't know how I'm going
to match this type of food

00:58:58.380 --> 00:58:59.400 align:middle line:90%
when I get back home.

00:58:59.400 --> 00:59:12.050 align:middle line:90%


00:59:12.050 --> 00:59:14.900 align:middle line:84%
My stay in Japan is almost
over, and I'm starting

00:59:14.900 --> 00:59:16.880 align:middle line:90%
to get a little worried.

00:59:16.880 --> 00:59:19.770 align:middle line:84%
While it's easy and affordable
to eat healthy here,

00:59:19.770 --> 00:59:23.450 align:middle line:84%
doing the same thing back home
will be a different story.

00:59:23.450 --> 00:59:26.450 align:middle line:84%
If I'm stuck in the middle of
nowhere on a film set all day,

00:59:26.450 --> 00:59:28.970 align:middle line:84%
I don't think catering
will be offering green tea

00:59:28.970 --> 00:59:31.970 align:middle line:90%
and natto for lunch.

00:59:31.970 --> 00:59:34.580 align:middle line:84%
I thought back to the start
of my journey and my dinner

00:59:34.580 --> 00:59:36.180 align:middle line:90%
with Yuko and her family.

00:59:36.180 --> 00:59:38.560 align:middle line:84%
She mentioned making her
children a bento box,

00:59:38.560 --> 00:59:40.850 align:middle line:84%
a kind of Japanese
packed lunch, which

00:59:40.850 --> 00:59:43.130 align:middle line:90%
they took to school every day.

00:59:43.130 --> 00:59:46.580 align:middle line:84%
I called Yuko, and she
arranged for her friend Ryoko

00:59:46.580 --> 00:59:48.425 align:middle line:84%
to teach me how to
make a bento box.

00:59:48.425 --> 00:59:50.840 align:middle line:90%


00:59:50.840 --> 00:59:51.640 align:middle line:90%
Oh, I know.

00:59:51.640 --> 00:59:52.880 align:middle line:90%
I know this.

00:59:52.880 --> 00:59:53.680 align:middle line:90%
Gobo.

00:59:53.680 --> 00:59:54.100 align:middle line:90%
>> Gobo.

00:59:54.100 --> 00:59:54.900 align:middle line:90%
>> Gobo.

00:59:54.900 --> 00:59:55.840 align:middle line:90%
>> Cut.

00:59:55.840 --> 00:59:57.370 align:middle line:90%
>> And cut in the center?

00:59:57.370 --> 00:59:58.740 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

00:59:58.740 --> 01:00:01.090 align:middle line:90%
>> And we make a finger puppet.

01:00:01.090 --> 01:00:02.500 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

01:00:02.500 --> 01:00:03.820 align:middle line:90%
You turn it-- OK.

01:00:03.820 --> 01:00:04.620 align:middle line:90%
That's amazing.

01:00:04.620 --> 01:00:06.580 align:middle line:90%
OK, can I?

01:00:06.580 --> 01:00:09.640 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, you make a hole in
the center, and then you--

01:00:09.640 --> 01:00:12.670 align:middle line:90%


01:00:12.670 --> 01:00:13.520 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah?

01:00:13.520 --> 01:00:13.790 align:middle line:90%
OK.

01:00:13.790 --> 01:00:14.020 align:middle line:90%
Konjaku.

01:00:14.020 --> 01:00:15.070 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING JAPANESE]

01:00:15.070 --> 01:00:15.640 align:middle line:90%
>> What?

01:00:15.640 --> 01:00:16.150 align:middle line:90%
OK.

01:00:16.150 --> 01:00:17.240 align:middle line:90%
OK, all right.

01:00:17.240 --> 01:00:18.600 align:middle line:90%
Oh, OK.

01:00:18.600 --> 01:00:20.770 align:middle line:84%
Don't look over
here for a second.

01:00:20.770 --> 01:00:21.990 align:middle line:90%
OK.

01:00:21.990 --> 01:00:22.790 align:middle line:90%
>> No, nothing.

01:00:22.790 --> 01:00:23.590 align:middle line:90%
OK.

01:00:23.590 --> 01:00:24.430 align:middle line:90%
Good.

01:00:24.430 --> 01:00:25.360 align:middle line:90%
In.

01:00:25.360 --> 01:00:26.000 align:middle line:90%
gobo?

01:00:26.000 --> 01:00:26.800 align:middle line:90%
>> Gobo.

01:00:26.800 --> 01:00:28.762 align:middle line:90%
>> Gobo.

01:00:28.762 --> 01:00:29.890 align:middle line:90%
In it goes.

01:00:29.890 --> 01:00:30.790 align:middle line:90%
gobo.

01:00:30.790 --> 01:00:34.580 align:middle line:90%
Bamboo shoot in there.

01:00:34.580 --> 01:00:37.440 align:middle line:84%
To be completely honest, I'm
not sure what I'm making here.

01:00:37.440 --> 01:00:39.410 align:middle line:84%
But I'm using the
same ingredients

01:00:39.410 --> 01:00:41.660 align:middle line:84%
that Yuko used for
her dinner, so I'm

01:00:41.660 --> 01:00:45.680 align:middle line:84%
pretty confident that this is
going to be a healthy lunch.

01:00:45.680 --> 01:00:48.530 align:middle line:84%
We've boiled and
washed the spinach.

01:00:48.530 --> 01:00:49.940 align:middle line:90%
And now we slice it up.

01:00:49.940 --> 01:00:54.920 align:middle line:84%
And it's going into sesame
that I've just grounded up.

01:00:54.920 --> 01:00:56.180 align:middle line:90%
So this is tamagoyaki.

01:00:56.180 --> 01:00:57.775 align:middle line:90%
It's like an omelet.

01:00:57.775 --> 01:01:02.410 align:middle line:90%
Man, this is upper level.

01:01:02.410 --> 01:01:03.885 align:middle line:90%
This?

01:01:03.885 --> 01:01:05.140 align:middle line:90%
In it goes.

01:01:05.140 --> 01:01:07.430 align:middle line:90%
OK, OK, OK.

01:01:07.430 --> 01:01:08.450 align:middle line:90%
All right, good.

01:01:08.450 --> 01:01:09.396 align:middle line:90%
Under.

01:01:09.396 --> 01:01:10.196 align:middle line:90%
>> Under.

01:01:10.196 --> 01:01:12.234 align:middle line:90%
>> Under.

01:01:12.234 --> 01:01:13.350 align:middle line:90%
Under.

01:01:13.350 --> 01:01:16.550 align:middle line:84%
So you just lift it up
and let it fall under.

01:01:16.550 --> 01:01:19.012 align:middle line:90%
Ho, this is the worst part.

01:01:19.012 --> 01:01:23.220 align:middle line:90%
>> [SPEAKING JAPANESE]

01:01:23.220 --> 01:01:24.663 align:middle line:90%
>> I can see what you're doing.

01:01:24.663 --> 01:01:25.580 align:middle line:90%
I don't know if I can.

01:01:25.580 --> 01:01:26.430 align:middle line:90%
OK.

01:01:26.430 --> 01:01:27.470 align:middle line:90%
Quickly.

01:01:27.470 --> 01:01:28.270 align:middle line:90%
>> [EXCLAIMS]

01:01:28.270 --> 01:01:31.035 align:middle line:90%
>> Hey.

01:01:31.035 --> 01:01:31.835 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

01:01:31.835 --> 01:01:38.280 align:middle line:90%


01:01:38.280 --> 01:01:40.790 align:middle line:84%
With all of the individual
ingredients prepared,

01:01:40.790 --> 01:01:43.200 align:middle line:84%
it's time to build
the bento boxes.

01:01:43.200 --> 01:01:45.660 align:middle line:84%
Like most Japanese
meals, the bento box

01:01:45.660 --> 01:01:50.136 align:middle line:84%
consists of a lot of small
side dishes and vegetables.

01:01:50.136 --> 01:01:51.330 align:middle line:90%
Oh, look at that.

01:01:51.330 --> 01:01:52.480 align:middle line:90%
That is beautiful.

01:01:52.480 --> 01:01:57.240 align:middle line:84%
We have our omelet
called tamagoyaki.

01:01:57.240 --> 01:01:59.220 align:middle line:84%
We've got all of our
vegetables there.

01:01:59.220 --> 01:02:01.380 align:middle line:90%
And we have a plum.

01:02:01.380 --> 01:02:04.110 align:middle line:84%
We have our rice
with nori on top.

01:02:04.110 --> 01:02:08.880 align:middle line:84%
And then underneath we have
kombu, another type of seaweed,

01:02:08.880 --> 01:02:11.850 align:middle line:90%
green goodness.

01:02:11.850 --> 01:02:14.370 align:middle line:84%
Now that I know how
to make the bento box,

01:02:14.370 --> 01:02:17.151 align:middle line:84%
I need to buy one of my
own to take home with me.

01:02:17.151 --> 01:02:19.920 align:middle line:90%


01:02:19.920 --> 01:02:23.040 align:middle line:90%
That's pretty cute.

01:02:23.040 --> 01:02:26.020 align:middle line:84%
They don't really
have a boy's one.

01:02:26.020 --> 01:02:26.820 align:middle line:90%
But I don't mind.

01:02:26.820 --> 01:02:27.620 align:middle line:90%
I like this.

01:02:27.620 --> 01:02:33.700 align:middle line:90%


01:02:33.700 --> 01:02:37.510 align:middle line:84%
Today I sort of
solved a big problem.

01:02:37.510 --> 01:02:45.970 align:middle line:84%
I now know I can take bento on
to my work, my weird, random,

01:02:45.970 --> 01:02:48.760 align:middle line:84%
"who knows what day where
I'm going to be" type work.

01:02:48.760 --> 01:02:52.028 align:middle line:84%
And I can open it up and just
have it at my regular times.

01:02:52.028 --> 01:02:54.070 align:middle line:84%
So that's going to solve
a lot of problems for me

01:02:54.070 --> 01:02:56.200 align:middle line:84%
when I get back and I
am stressed about what

01:02:56.200 --> 01:02:57.310 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to do every day.

01:02:57.310 --> 01:02:58.730 align:middle line:90%
I pack.

01:02:58.730 --> 01:03:02.410 align:middle line:84%
I can be self-sufficient, pretty
much, for one, even two meals

01:03:02.410 --> 01:03:04.990 align:middle line:84%
throughout the day,
and then just make sure

01:03:04.990 --> 01:03:07.570 align:middle line:84%
I get home to prepare my
other meal, or if I'm out,

01:03:07.570 --> 01:03:12.350 align:middle line:84%
at a place that sells sushi or
the type of food I need to get.

01:03:12.350 --> 01:03:13.150 align:middle line:90%
I can do that.

01:03:13.150 --> 01:03:17.860 align:middle line:90%


01:03:17.860 --> 01:03:20.740 align:middle line:84%
I've been in Japan now
for almost two weeks.

01:03:20.740 --> 01:03:23.680 align:middle line:84%
And I think that I've got
the food thing figured out.

01:03:23.680 --> 01:03:27.130 align:middle line:84%
I feel confident in knowing
what to eat and what to avoid.

01:03:27.130 --> 01:03:30.730 align:middle line:84%
Shopping and cooking for myself
has become a habit, and foods

01:03:30.730 --> 01:03:32.620 align:middle line:84%
that I would never
have eaten back home--

01:03:32.620 --> 01:03:36.400 align:middle line:84%
tofu, pickled vegetables,
green tea, even natto--

01:03:36.400 --> 01:03:38.680 align:middle line:90%
now feel normal to me.

01:03:38.680 --> 01:03:40.630 align:middle line:84%
And most importantly,
I'm keeping

01:03:40.630 --> 01:03:42.265 align:middle line:90%
an eye on my portion sizes.

01:03:42.265 --> 01:03:44.890 align:middle line:90%


01:03:44.890 --> 01:03:46.840 align:middle line:90%
Oh.

01:03:46.840 --> 01:03:49.000 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

01:03:49.000 --> 01:03:53.730 align:middle line:90%
So I just lost my pants.

01:03:53.730 --> 01:03:55.720 align:middle line:90%
When I'm carrying bags--

01:03:55.720 --> 01:03:56.593 align:middle line:90%
there's good news.

01:03:56.593 --> 01:03:57.760 align:middle line:90%
We're heading to the temple.

01:03:57.760 --> 01:04:02.200 align:middle line:90%
But my pants have become looser.

01:04:02.200 --> 01:04:06.010 align:middle line:84%
It means they fall down when
I'm not able to hitch them up

01:04:06.010 --> 01:04:07.370 align:middle line:90%
as I'm walking.

01:04:07.370 --> 01:04:09.387 align:middle line:90%
So yeah.

01:04:09.387 --> 01:04:10.220 align:middle line:90%
Where do I put this?

01:04:10.220 --> 01:04:11.020 align:middle line:90%
How do I--

01:04:11.020 --> 01:04:14.370 align:middle line:90%


01:04:14.370 --> 01:04:17.430 align:middle line:84%
It's my final weekend in
Japan, and the crew and I

01:04:17.430 --> 01:04:19.710 align:middle line:84%
are spending it at a
Zen Buddhist temple

01:04:19.710 --> 01:04:22.050 align:middle line:90%
a few hours out of Tokyo.

01:04:22.050 --> 01:04:24.990 align:middle line:84%
I feel like I've learned
a lot about Japan's food

01:04:24.990 --> 01:04:26.790 align:middle line:90%
and lifestyle.

01:04:26.790 --> 01:04:29.190 align:middle line:84%
If I can stay motivated
once I get home,

01:04:29.190 --> 01:04:31.860 align:middle line:84%
I know this diet
will be a success.

01:04:31.860 --> 01:04:34.440 align:middle line:84%
I'm hoping a Buddhist monk
can give me some guidance

01:04:34.440 --> 01:04:35.565 align:middle line:90%
and help me stay focused.

01:04:35.565 --> 01:04:38.300 align:middle line:90%


01:04:38.300 --> 01:04:42.560 align:middle line:84%
Konishiki, when he visited
the temple last week,

01:04:42.560 --> 01:04:45.170 align:middle line:84%
there's some sort
of ritual where

01:04:45.170 --> 01:04:46.640 align:middle line:90%
they hit you with a stick.

01:04:46.640 --> 01:04:49.910 align:middle line:84%
And because he's
Konishiki and a big guy,

01:04:49.910 --> 01:04:52.460 align:middle line:84%
they went and got a really
big stick, a thick one,

01:04:52.460 --> 01:04:54.260 align:middle line:90%
and they hit him really hard.

01:04:54.260 --> 01:04:57.230 align:middle line:90%
And it welted and became black.

01:04:57.230 --> 01:05:00.230 align:middle line:84%
It was a very painful
mark that they left.

01:05:00.230 --> 01:05:03.897 align:middle line:84%
And he says they were
doing it for comedy.

01:05:03.897 --> 01:05:05.480 align:middle line:84%
So I'm a little bit
worried, because I

01:05:05.480 --> 01:05:10.130 align:middle line:84%
think probably the temple's
been briefed that I'm a comedian

01:05:10.130 --> 01:05:12.630 align:middle line:84%
and there's going
to be a film crew.

01:05:12.630 --> 01:05:17.090 align:middle line:84%
So I'm worried
that the monk, he's

01:05:17.090 --> 01:05:23.780 align:middle line:84%
going to hit me harder,
because it's funny to do that.

01:05:23.780 --> 01:05:25.850 align:middle line:84%
We've stopped at a
roadside diner for lunch.

01:05:25.850 --> 01:05:27.950 align:middle line:84%
And I'm pleasantly
surprised to find that even

01:05:27.950 --> 01:05:32.660 align:middle line:84%
here healthy meal options
are readily available.

01:05:32.660 --> 01:05:36.920 align:middle line:84%
This is from a roadside
diner in Japan.

01:05:36.920 --> 01:05:40.310 align:middle line:84%
The crew have been able to order
slightly more exciting meals,

01:05:40.310 --> 01:05:43.410 align:middle line:84%
with deep-fried stuff and
burgers and western things.

01:05:43.410 --> 01:05:47.990 align:middle line:84%
But this is what I can get
at a diner in the roadside

01:05:47.990 --> 01:05:50.750 align:middle line:90%
along a highway in Japan.

01:05:50.750 --> 01:05:53.130 align:middle line:90%
So it's very exciting.

01:05:53.130 --> 01:05:56.130 align:middle line:84%
If I was in Australia
and I was pulling over,

01:05:56.130 --> 01:05:59.620 align:middle line:84%
I'd be eating burgers and
sandwiches and hot chips.

01:05:59.620 --> 01:06:02.800 align:middle line:84%
But this is what I got
here, a very healthy meal.

01:06:02.800 --> 01:06:06.080 align:middle line:90%


01:06:06.080 --> 01:06:09.380 align:middle line:84%
With lunch out of the way we
continue to the temple high

01:06:09.380 --> 01:06:10.820 align:middle line:90%
in the mountains west of Tokyo.

01:06:10.820 --> 01:06:16.570 align:middle line:90%


