01:14:55.550 --> 01:14:59.810 align:middle line:90%


01:14:59.810 --> 01:15:00.990 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

01:15:00.990 --> 01:15:01.830 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, nice.

01:15:01.830 --> 01:15:15.240 align:middle line:90%


01:15:15.240 --> 01:15:18.810 align:middle line:84%
Today Asami will teach me
more meditation techniques.

01:15:18.810 --> 01:15:22.500 align:middle line:84%
But first, he has a
little gift for me.

01:15:22.500 --> 01:15:24.930 align:middle line:84%
As you may have noticed,
I'm now wearing suspenders.

01:15:24.930 --> 01:15:27.660 align:middle line:90%
I'm not in a 1993 music video.

01:15:27.660 --> 01:15:30.840 align:middle line:84%
I am wearing suspenders
because the monk,

01:15:30.840 --> 01:15:33.615 align:middle line:84%
after my pants fell down
embarrassingly in the kitchen

01:15:33.615 --> 01:15:35.490 align:middle line:84%
when I was trying to
help him in the kitchen,

01:15:35.490 --> 01:15:36.915 align:middle line:90%
he said he had suspenders.

01:15:36.915 --> 01:15:39.540 align:middle line:84%
And he went and found them, and
he gave them to me this morning

01:15:39.540 --> 01:15:40.440 align:middle line:90%
as a gift.

01:15:40.440 --> 01:15:42.148 align:middle line:84%
I'll have to check if
he wants them back.

01:15:42.148 --> 01:15:44.667 align:middle line:84%
But if he doesn't, I'll
be wearing some suspenders

01:15:44.667 --> 01:15:46.500 align:middle line:84%
with these jeans now,
because the jeans have

01:15:46.500 --> 01:15:49.660 align:middle line:84%
become quite loose in the
time I've been in Japan.

01:15:49.660 --> 01:15:53.280 align:middle line:84%
So it's both exciting
and a real bonus.

01:15:53.280 --> 01:15:56.591 align:middle line:90%


01:15:56.591 --> 01:15:58.010 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh.

01:15:58.010 --> 01:15:59.540 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

01:15:59.540 --> 01:16:01.050 align:middle line:90%
That's all right.

01:16:01.050 --> 01:16:02.890 align:middle line:90%
>> That's good.

01:16:02.890 --> 01:16:03.800 align:middle line:90%
OK.

01:16:03.800 --> 01:16:06.030 align:middle line:84%
Asami tells me
today's lesson will

01:16:06.030 --> 01:16:08.910 align:middle line:84%
be more enlightening than
tracing the [? ku. ?]

01:16:08.910 --> 01:16:11.280 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden
I'm a bit nervous.

01:16:11.280 --> 01:16:23.250 align:middle line:90%


01:16:23.250 --> 01:16:25.710 align:middle line:84%
I'm told this technique
will help me stay focused

01:16:25.710 --> 01:16:27.180 align:middle line:90%
and keep my mind clear.

01:16:27.180 --> 01:16:29.970 align:middle line:84%
But I seem to be getting
whacked more than the others.

01:16:29.970 --> 01:16:32.490 align:middle line:90%


01:16:32.490 --> 01:16:35.040 align:middle line:84%
I wonder if this is Asami's
way of telling me to keep quiet

01:16:35.040 --> 01:16:36.285 align:middle line:90%
about his Mos Burger habits.

01:16:36.285 --> 01:16:51.470 align:middle line:90%


01:16:51.470 --> 01:16:55.250 align:middle line:84%
With my Zen training complete,
it's time to fly home.

01:16:55.250 --> 01:16:57.860 align:middle line:84%
My journey here has
taught me a lot of things.

01:16:57.860 --> 01:17:01.190 align:middle line:84%
It's taught me that eating
healthy can also be delicious,

01:17:01.190 --> 01:17:03.860 align:middle line:84%
and that daily exercise
and portion control

01:17:03.860 --> 01:17:08.060 align:middle line:84%
can mean the difference
between slim and sumo.

01:17:08.060 --> 01:17:10.760 align:middle line:84%
Now it's up to me to
take this knowledge home

01:17:10.760 --> 01:17:11.900 align:middle line:90%
and apply it to my life.

01:17:11.900 --> 01:17:23.756 align:middle line:90%


01:17:23.756 --> 01:17:24.780 align:middle line:90%
Come on.

01:17:24.780 --> 01:17:26.310 align:middle line:90%
Go for a walk?

01:17:26.310 --> 01:17:27.260 align:middle line:90%
Come on.

01:17:27.260 --> 01:17:28.390 align:middle line:90%
Come on.

01:17:28.390 --> 01:17:30.220 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, good boy.

01:17:30.220 --> 01:17:31.020 align:middle line:90%
Good boy.

01:17:31.020 --> 01:17:31.820 align:middle line:90%
Come on.

01:17:31.820 --> 01:17:33.697 align:middle line:90%


01:17:33.697 --> 01:17:35.280 align:middle line:84%
I've been home for
a little while now,

01:17:35.280 --> 01:17:37.290 align:middle line:84%
and I've been wondering
how to integrate what I

01:17:37.290 --> 01:17:40.590 align:middle line:90%
learned into my daily routine.

01:17:40.590 --> 01:17:43.530 align:middle line:84%
Each day in Japan I was walking
almost twice the distance

01:17:43.530 --> 01:17:46.100 align:middle line:84%
I was before I
started this diet.

01:17:46.100 --> 01:17:48.210 align:middle line:84%
And with a little
help from Malcolm here

01:17:48.210 --> 01:17:50.430 align:middle line:84%
I've been able to
keep that number up.

01:17:50.430 --> 01:17:52.900 align:middle line:84%
It's been great, and not
just for me, but for Malcolm

01:17:52.900 --> 01:17:53.700 align:middle line:90%
as well.

01:17:53.700 --> 01:17:56.373 align:middle line:84%
Because, between you
and me, he was starting

01:17:56.373 --> 01:17:57.540 align:middle line:90%
to gain a little bit chubby.

01:17:57.540 --> 01:18:00.600 align:middle line:90%


01:18:00.600 --> 01:18:02.490 align:middle line:90%
I've kept up my shopping habits.

01:18:02.490 --> 01:18:04.050 align:middle line:84%
And though the
big grocery chains

01:18:04.050 --> 01:18:06.760 align:middle line:84%
don't have a lot of the
more obscure food items,

01:18:06.760 --> 01:18:09.960 align:middle line:84%
I found an Asian grocer
nearby that stocks almost

01:18:09.960 --> 01:18:11.460 align:middle line:90%
everything I need.

01:18:11.460 --> 01:18:13.980 align:middle line:84%
I visit them so often now
that the owner told me

01:18:13.980 --> 01:18:15.900 align:middle line:90%
I was his biggest customer.

01:18:15.900 --> 01:18:17.640 align:middle line:90%
At first I was flattered.

01:18:17.640 --> 01:18:20.187 align:middle line:84%
And then I realized
he was making a joke.

01:18:20.187 --> 01:18:23.530 align:middle line:90%


01:18:23.530 --> 01:18:26.150 align:middle line:84%
I have a good source for
almost all the ingredients

01:18:26.150 --> 01:18:28.220 align:middle line:90%
I need to maintain my diet--

01:18:28.220 --> 01:18:31.910 align:middle line:84%
miso paste, tofu,
natto, fish flakes,

01:18:31.910 --> 01:18:35.882 align:middle line:84%
dried pickles, ume
plums, and konjaku.

01:18:35.882 --> 01:18:37.340 align:middle line:84%
Some of the fresh
veggies I wanted,

01:18:37.340 --> 01:18:40.130 align:middle line:84%
like daikon, gobo,
and bamboo shoots,

01:18:40.130 --> 01:18:41.600 align:middle line:90%
are a lot harder to track down.

01:18:41.600 --> 01:18:43.790 align:middle line:84%
So I have to make do
with what I can find.

01:18:43.790 --> 01:18:47.960 align:middle line:90%


01:18:47.960 --> 01:18:50.330 align:middle line:84%
I still need to spend long
hours in the edit room.

01:18:50.330 --> 01:18:52.740 align:middle line:84%
But I've replaced the
Coke with green tea.

01:18:52.740 --> 01:18:54.890 align:middle line:84%
And I feel like
snacking, I keep plenty

01:18:54.890 --> 01:18:57.080 align:middle line:90%
of edamame beans on hand.

01:18:57.080 --> 01:18:59.750 align:middle line:84%
They're delicious, high
in protein and vitamins,

01:18:59.750 --> 01:19:00.860 align:middle line:90%
and low in fat.

01:19:00.860 --> 01:19:03.850 align:middle line:90%
Plus, it's a fun word to say.

01:19:03.850 --> 01:19:04.650 align:middle line:90%
Edamame.

01:19:04.650 --> 01:19:08.840 align:middle line:90%


01:19:08.840 --> 01:19:10.550 align:middle line:84%
This evening I'm
helping a friend perform

01:19:10.550 --> 01:19:12.230 align:middle line:90%
at the Sydney Comedy Festival.

01:19:12.230 --> 01:19:13.910 align:middle line:90%
In the old days I'd have driven.

01:19:13.910 --> 01:19:15.560 align:middle line:84%
But it seems like
a nice evening,

01:19:15.560 --> 01:19:18.620 align:middle line:90%
so I've decided to walk instead.

01:19:18.620 --> 01:19:20.960 align:middle line:84%
I always run into old
friends at events like these.

01:19:20.960 --> 01:19:24.120 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes they want
to grab a bite to eat.

01:19:24.120 --> 01:19:25.730 align:middle line:84%
So I'm worried that
at this late hour

01:19:25.730 --> 01:19:29.360 align:middle line:84%
the only food options
will be greasy junk food.

01:19:29.360 --> 01:19:31.280 align:middle line:84%
But it turns out
my local sushi bar

01:19:31.280 --> 01:19:36.140 align:middle line:84%
has a back menu full of
traditional and healthy dishes.

01:19:36.140 --> 01:19:38.850 align:middle line:84%
So I've been to the
local sushi train.

01:19:38.850 --> 01:19:44.770 align:middle line:84%
So this is a whole
train of salmon, natto.

01:19:44.770 --> 01:19:50.460 align:middle line:84%
And you can also get
the pickled plum, ume,

01:19:50.460 --> 01:19:53.150 align:middle line:84%
which is what I stick in
my rice every morning.

01:19:53.150 --> 01:19:54.950 align:middle line:84%
You've just got to
work hard to find it.

01:19:54.950 --> 01:19:56.670 align:middle line:90%
You need just to ask.

01:19:56.670 --> 01:19:57.840 align:middle line:90%
Sushi train?

01:19:57.840 --> 01:19:59.520 align:middle line:90%
They put out stuff in the train.

01:19:59.520 --> 01:20:02.270 align:middle line:84%
But they put the big ones
out, the ones everyone wants.

01:20:02.270 --> 01:20:04.020 align:middle line:84%
Because they don't
want it to go to waste.

01:20:04.020 --> 01:20:06.350 align:middle line:84%
But the menu, that's
where you can get plum,

01:20:06.350 --> 01:20:09.420 align:middle line:90%
natto, and pickles.

01:20:09.420 --> 01:20:11.430 align:middle line:84%
It's great for nights
when I want to go out

01:20:11.430 --> 01:20:13.200 align:middle line:90%
or don't have time to cook.

01:20:13.200 --> 01:20:15.330 align:middle line:84%
Plus, the look on the
waitress' face the first time

01:20:15.330 --> 01:20:19.050 align:middle line:90%
I ordered natto was priceless.

01:20:19.050 --> 01:20:21.450 align:middle line:84%
For the most part,
adapting the Japanese diet

01:20:21.450 --> 01:20:24.930 align:middle line:84%
to fit my lifestyle has been
a fairly simple and painless

01:20:24.930 --> 01:20:26.250 align:middle line:90%
process.

01:20:26.250 --> 01:20:29.220 align:middle line:84%
Keeping it up for the remainder
of my 12-week experiment

01:20:29.220 --> 01:20:31.170 align:middle line:90%
shouldn't be a problem at all.

01:20:31.170 --> 01:20:36.350 align:middle line:84%
Unless something drastically
changes in my work life.

01:20:36.350 --> 01:20:37.910 align:middle line:84%
I've just checked
my emails, and I've

01:20:37.910 --> 01:20:40.640 align:middle line:84%
got a job coming up where
I'm directing a comedy

01:20:40.640 --> 01:20:43.400 align:middle line:90%
show starting in like two days.

01:20:43.400 --> 01:20:46.585 align:middle line:84%
So that's going to
be a lot of work,

01:20:46.585 --> 01:20:47.960 align:middle line:84%
and I'm going to
be on set a lot.

01:20:47.960 --> 01:20:52.280 align:middle line:84%
So I've been planning
how to do my morning

01:20:52.280 --> 01:20:55.560 align:middle line:84%
ritual to make sure I get
my bento box done in time.

01:20:55.560 --> 01:21:04.146 align:middle line:90%


01:21:04.146 --> 01:21:04.946 align:middle line:90%
Mm.

01:21:04.946 --> 01:21:10.380 align:middle line:90%


01:21:10.380 --> 01:21:12.730 align:middle line:84%
I'm making my bento
while I eat breakfast,

01:21:12.730 --> 01:21:18.440 align:middle line:84%
just because I have to save
some time in the morning.

01:21:18.440 --> 01:21:22.350 align:middle line:84%
And this is the plum that
I've put on in the rice.

01:21:22.350 --> 01:21:26.070 align:middle line:90%


01:21:26.070 --> 01:21:29.130 align:middle line:90%
So that is my rice component.

01:21:29.130 --> 01:21:30.750 align:middle line:90%
Done.

01:21:30.750 --> 01:21:33.390 align:middle line:84%
No I'll make the good
side of the bento box.

01:21:33.390 --> 01:21:36.700 align:middle line:84%
Because I'm not a big rice
eater, I love this part.

01:21:36.700 --> 01:21:38.950 align:middle line:84%
This has got all the protein
and the vegetables in it.

01:21:38.950 --> 01:21:41.060 align:middle line:90%


01:21:41.060 --> 01:21:41.860 align:middle line:90%
Konjaku.

01:21:41.860 --> 01:21:44.703 align:middle line:90%


01:21:44.703 --> 01:21:45.503 align:middle line:90%
Carrot.

01:21:45.503 --> 01:21:49.340 align:middle line:90%


01:21:49.340 --> 01:21:51.570 align:middle line:84%
I'm building my bento
box for the day.

01:21:51.570 --> 01:21:54.860 align:middle line:84%
And I'm also making a little
brown rice, tofu, and avocado

01:21:54.860 --> 01:21:57.690 align:middle line:90%
sushi roll as a snack.

01:21:57.690 --> 01:22:00.150 align:middle line:84%
And I can't forget about
the miso soup and thermos

01:22:00.150 --> 01:22:00.950 align:middle line:90%
of green tea.

01:22:00.950 --> 01:22:08.200 align:middle line:90%


01:22:08.200 --> 01:22:10.030 align:middle line:84%
Aside from all
the extra walking,

01:22:10.030 --> 01:22:13.780 align:middle line:84%
I also like to start my days
now with some light exercise

01:22:13.780 --> 01:22:17.230 align:middle line:84%
followed by my usual trip
to the local swimming pool.

01:22:17.230 --> 01:22:18.940 align:middle line:90%
But not just to shower.

01:22:18.940 --> 01:22:21.640 align:middle line:84%
Now I like to swim
a few laps first.

01:22:21.640 --> 01:22:23.060 align:middle line:90%
Swimming at a swimming pool--

01:22:23.060 --> 01:22:23.860 align:middle line:90%
who'd have guessed?

01:22:23.860 --> 01:22:29.610 align:middle line:90%


01:22:29.610 --> 01:22:33.317 align:middle line:84%
So today we're filming in a
house in a suburb in Sydney.

01:22:33.317 --> 01:22:35.400 align:middle line:84%
There's always a lot of
temptation in the morning,

01:22:35.400 --> 01:22:37.790 align:middle line:84%
because the first
things that happened

01:22:37.790 --> 01:22:39.300 align:middle line:84%
is they lay out
all the hot food,

01:22:39.300 --> 01:22:43.822 align:middle line:84%
and everyone just sits and eat
while I wait for them to start.

01:22:43.822 --> 01:22:45.780 align:middle line:84%
But I still have to get
here at the right time,

01:22:45.780 --> 01:22:47.490 align:middle line:84%
because I'm the guy
who picks the space.

01:22:47.490 --> 01:22:51.070 align:middle line:84%
And then we move, and they start
slowly building and eating.

01:22:51.070 --> 01:22:54.180 align:middle line:84%
So I have to sit and wait
for them to finish eating.

01:22:54.180 --> 01:23:00.100 align:middle line:90%


01:23:00.100 --> 01:23:02.490 align:middle line:90%
But lucky I have natto.

01:23:02.490 --> 01:23:09.670 align:middle line:90%
So it's keeping me sustained.

01:23:09.670 --> 01:23:12.040 align:middle line:84%
I would love you
guys to still be

01:23:12.040 --> 01:23:15.230 align:middle line:90%
orientated towards the screens.

01:23:15.230 --> 01:23:16.280 align:middle line:90%
So pathetic, yeah.

01:23:16.280 --> 01:23:18.940 align:middle line:84%
And like, oh, look at what
this person is up to, yeah.

01:23:18.940 --> 01:23:21.070 align:middle line:90%
And then maybe--

01:23:21.070 --> 01:23:22.900 align:middle line:84%
Directing is one of
my biggest passions,

01:23:22.900 --> 01:23:24.580 align:middle line:90%
especially directing comedy.

01:23:24.580 --> 01:23:27.070 align:middle line:84%
But lunch on set
requires discipline.

01:23:27.070 --> 01:23:29.770 align:middle line:90%
The catered meals smell good--

01:23:29.770 --> 01:23:32.250 align:middle line:90%
really good.

01:23:32.250 --> 01:23:34.290 align:middle line:90%
Well, it's lunchtime on set.

01:23:34.290 --> 01:23:37.880 align:middle line:84%
And everyone's got their
lunch that's been catered for.

01:23:37.880 --> 01:23:46.020 align:middle line:84%
But I've got my
rice and bento box.

01:23:46.020 --> 01:23:47.610 align:middle line:90%
Everyone's very supportive.

01:23:47.610 --> 01:23:48.660 align:middle line:90%
They're teasing me today.

01:23:48.660 --> 01:23:51.020 align:middle line:84%
But normally they'd
be very supportive.

01:23:51.020 --> 01:23:57.187 align:middle line:90%


01:23:57.187 --> 01:23:59.270 align:middle line:84%
>> We're just going to go
all get [INAUDIBLE] mash

01:23:59.270 --> 01:23:59.520 align:middle line:90%
[INAUDIBLE]

01:23:59.520 --> 01:24:00.430 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, enjoy it.

01:24:00.430 --> 01:24:02.500 align:middle line:90%
I don't care.

01:24:02.500 --> 01:24:07.414 align:middle line:84%
People make fun of me and
get to eat mashed potato.

01:24:07.414 --> 01:24:09.803 align:middle line:90%
I don't care.

01:24:09.803 --> 01:24:10.720 align:middle line:90%
Who wants to try some?

01:24:10.720 --> 01:24:12.740 align:middle line:90%
You can try some.

01:24:12.740 --> 01:24:13.540 align:middle line:90%
Come on, man.

01:24:13.540 --> 01:24:14.690 align:middle line:90%
You want some?

01:24:14.690 --> 01:24:15.747 align:middle line:90%
Do you want to try it?

01:24:15.747 --> 01:24:23.870 align:middle line:90%


01:24:23.870 --> 01:24:27.470 align:middle line:84%
I cook easy Japanese meals
every evening after work.

01:24:27.470 --> 01:24:30.320 align:middle line:84%
And tamagoyaki is a
simple dish to make.

01:24:30.320 --> 01:24:33.050 align:middle line:84%
I don't have a square pan,
but my round frying pan

01:24:33.050 --> 01:24:35.010 align:middle line:90%
will get the job done.

01:24:35.010 --> 01:24:36.935 align:middle line:90%
It's not pretty, but it works.

01:24:36.935 --> 01:24:39.460 align:middle line:90%


01:24:39.460 --> 01:24:41.385 align:middle line:84%
It's so nerve
racking, the bit where

01:24:41.385 --> 01:24:43.080 align:middle line:84%
you have to pick it
up and get the thing

01:24:43.080 --> 01:24:45.285 align:middle line:90%
to slide under in time.

01:24:45.285 --> 01:24:47.160 align:middle line:84%
Because if you don't,
it just starts cooking,

01:24:47.160 --> 01:24:49.050 align:middle line:90%
and it doesn't slide anymore.

01:24:49.050 --> 01:24:51.480 align:middle line:84%
But I made it, so
crisis averted.

01:24:51.480 --> 01:24:55.930 align:middle line:90%


01:24:55.930 --> 01:24:56.730 align:middle line:90%
OK, cut.

01:24:56.730 --> 01:24:57.530 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, let's do it.

01:24:57.530 --> 01:24:58.500 align:middle line:90%
Let's shoot that.

01:24:58.500 --> 01:25:00.000 align:middle line:84%
Can I get you
starting further back?

01:25:00.000 --> 01:25:02.860 align:middle line:90%
Everyone starting further back?

01:25:02.860 --> 01:25:05.500 align:middle line:84%
Directing the comedy program
over the past few weeks

01:25:05.500 --> 01:25:06.730 align:middle line:90%
has been hectic.

01:25:06.730 --> 01:25:10.220 align:middle line:84%
But through it all I've managed
to stay true to my diet--

01:25:10.220 --> 01:25:13.030 align:middle line:84%
natto for breakfast,
followed by exercise,

01:25:13.030 --> 01:25:16.960 align:middle line:84%
then my morning stroll,
swim, and shower.

01:25:16.960 --> 01:25:19.480 align:middle line:84%
I prepare my bento box
daily to eat on set.

01:25:19.480 --> 01:25:24.820 align:middle line:84%
And cooking meals has become
a part of my daily life.

01:25:24.820 --> 01:25:28.520 align:middle line:84%
This Japanese way of eating
no longer feels like a diet.

01:25:28.520 --> 01:25:30.400 align:middle line:84%
I eat every meal
with chopsticks,

01:25:30.400 --> 01:25:33.820 align:middle line:84%
and drinking nothing but green
tea has become second nature.

01:25:33.820 --> 01:25:38.880 align:middle line:90%


